==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Erebus
<hw>Er"e*bus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Greek Myth.)</fld> <def>A place of nether
darkness, being the gloomy space through which the souls passed to
Hades. See <xex>Milton's</xex> ⟦ldquo⟧Paradise Lost,⟦rdquo⟧ Book II.,
line 883.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Greek Myth.)</fld> <def>The son of Chaos and
brother of <er>Nox</er>, who dwelt in Erebus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To the infernal deep, with <qex>Erebus</qex> and tortures
vile.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erect</ent>⟦br⟧
